// @run
// @log 0
// KNOWN-UNSOUND — xfail (ROADMAP A13: "soundness of the hole-operand rule is
// permissive — doesn't yet reject `i32 + string`").
//
// `add`'s params are inference holes. A `+` on a hole operand currently returns
// the operand type and DEFERS concretization to the call site, but the call site
// does not re-check that the two concrete argument types are actually addable.
// So `add(1, "x")` type-checks with ZERO errors and runs, producing a garbage
// `0` instead of being rejected.
//
// TODO(soundness): this should be a `@error expected i32, got "x"` (or similar)
// once the call-site monomorphization validates hole-operand binary ops. When
// that lands, flip this file to `// @check` + `// @error` and drop the `@log`.
// It is captured as `@run`/`@log 0` today so the CONTRACT GAP is pinned: the
// regression guard will fire (log mismatch or new error) the moment behavior
// changes, surfacing the fix at merge.
function add(a, b) a + b
print(add(1, "x"))               // 0  (UNSOUND: should not type-check at all)
